# Get the input
phrase = input()

# Split the phrase into a list of words
words = phrase.split()

# Set up a variable to track whether or not a word is repeated
repeated = False

# Loop through all of the words
for word in words:
    # Count how many times the word is in the phrase
    count = words.count(word)

    # If the count is greater than 1, a word is repeated
    if count > 1:
        repeated = True

# Print the output based on whether or not a word is repeated
if repeated:
    print("no")
else:
    print("yes")
